gs of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert de boson of Devonshire married Robert de Boson before 1265, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1240–1285":"1240–1285","1265–Male":"1265–Surnud","1270–1286":"1270–1286","1270–1295":"1270–1295","–Female":"Surnud","about 1270":"umbes 1270","Abt 1270?":"umbes 1270","before 1265":"enne 1265","1265":"1265","1286":"1286","1285":"1285","1295":"1295","1240":"1240","about 1265":"umbes 1265","1270":"1270","Ilton, Somerset, England":"Ilton, Somerset, England","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1240–1285":"1240–1285","1265–Male":"1265–Kuollut","1270–1286":"1270–1286","1270–1295":"1270–1295","–Female":"Kuollut","about 1270":"noin 1270","Abt 1270?":"noin 1270","before 1265":"ennen vuotta 1265","1265":"1265","1286":"1286","1285":"1285","1295":"1295","1240":"1240","about 1265":"noin 1265","1270":"1270","Ilton, Somerset, England":"Ilton, Somerset, England","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1240–1285":"1240–1285","1265–Male":"1265–Décédé","1270–1286":"1270–1286","1270–1295":"1270–1295","–Female":"Décédée","about 1270":"environ 1270","Abt 1270?":"environ 1270","before 1265":"avant 1265","1265":"1265","1286":"1286","1285":"1285","1295":"1295","1240":"1240","about 1265":"environ 1265","1270":"1270","Ilton, Somerset, England":"Ilton, Somerset, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert de boson of Devonshire a épousé Robert de Boson avant 1265, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils et 2 filles."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1240–1285":"1240–1285","1265–Male":"1265–Verstorben","127